text: The 1936 Florida gubernatorial election was held on November 3, 1936. Democratic nominee Fred P. Cone defeated Republican nominee E.E. Callaway with 80.91% of the vote. ==Primary elections== Primary elections were held on June 2, 1936. ===Democratic primary=== ====Candidates==== *Fred P. Cone, former State Senator *W. Raleigh Petteway, Judge of the Criminal Court of Record for Hillsborough County *William C. Hodges, State Senator *Jerry W. Carter *B. F. Paty *Dan Chappell *Grady Burton *Peter Tomasello Jr. *Stafford Caldwell *Amos Lewis *Mallie Martin *Carl Maples *Redmond B. Gautier *J. R. Yearwood ====Results==== ==General election== ===Candidates=== *Fred P. Cone, Democratic *E.E. Callaway, Republican ===Results=== ==References== 1936 Florida Gubernatorial
title: 1936 Florida gubernatorial election
